docs/archive/
# ===== end fractary-docs =====
codex/cache/

# ===== fractary-faber (managed) =====
# faber/runs/plan.json IS committed (deterministic, safe to share)
# faber/runs/state-*.json are EXCLUDED during active runs to prevent git-reversion
#   — a `git pull` during an active workflow would revert a tracked state file to
#     an older committed version, causing silent loss of progress and fabrication risk.
#   — State files are force-committed only at Phase 4 finalization (workflow complete).
#   — To commit a completed state file: git add -f .fractary/faber/runs/{plan_id}/state-*.json
faber/runs/*/state-*.json
# .active-run-id is worktree-local state and must NOT be committed
faber/runs/.active-run-id
# ===== end fractary-faber =====
